<!-- Hybrid Off Canvas -->
<div id="hybrid-offcanvas-menu" class="offcanvas-menu oc-yeast">
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <span class="x-trigger show-offcanvas"><%= partial "partials/svg/x" %></span>
    <h3 class="oc-heading">Hybrids (Better than a Prius).</h3>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="oc-information">
        <div class="oc-summary">
          <span class="mini-heading">The Inbetweeners</span>
          <p class="mini-body">
          A hybrid beer is either a beer fermented with lager yeast at warm
          (ale) temperatures or a beer fermented with ale yeast at cool (lager)
          temperatures. These beers are a breed of their own. Brewers have their
          own ways of creating the brew's characteristics through exact lengths
          and temperatures of fermentation.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="oc-characteristics">
          <span class="mini-heading">Characteristics</span>
          <ul class="mini-body characteristic-list">
            <li class="characteristic">Warm fermented ale yeasts produce fruit flavors and fruity/floral esters (aromas)</li>
            <li class="characteristic">Cold fermented ale yeasts produce less esters and results in a more refined beer reminiscent of a lager</li>
            <li class="characteristic">Characteristics tend to be dependent on the style of beer</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="oc-example-beers">
